10. Meghan Markle #MeghanMarkle  Actress and humanitarian. Currently engaged to Prince Harry. Global ambassador for World Vision Canada. Outspoken advocate for gender equality and women's rights. A UN Women advocate and proud feminist.pic.twitter.com/GD9iyx4gDU

9. Ava Duvernay (@ava) #AvaDuvernay  American film director, producer, and screenwriter. The first African American woman to win the U.S Directing Award. First black female director to be nominated for a #GoldenGlobe Award. And the first to be nominated for an #AcademyAward .pic.twitter.com/qWyuyeqjGQ

8. Rowan Blanchard (@RowanBlanchard) #RowanBlanchard  American actress and activist. Her areas of #activism include #feminism, #humanrights, and #gunviolence. She has spoken at the UN Women and US National Committee's annual conference as part of #TeamHeforShe .pic.twitter.com/JgALZRHlJV

7. Maya Angelou (@DrMayaAngelou) #MayaAngelou  American poet, author, and #civilrights activist. She's best known for her memoir, I Know Why the Caged Bird Sings. Which was the first nonfiction bestseller by an African American woman.pic.twitter.com/aYcfyQKzeu

6. Laverne Cox (@Lavernecox) #LaverneCox  American actress, producer, and #LGBT advocate. She is the first openly #transgender person to be nominated for a Primetime Emmy Award for acting, and the first to win a Daytime #Emmy as an executive producer.pic.twitter.com/6fBWTCRV40
5. Gloria Steinem (@GloriaSteinem) #GloriaSteinem  Feminist, journalist and social political activist. Co-founded Ms. magazine and Women's Media Center.pic.twitter.com/klqsgmzvW7

4. Emma Watson (@EmmaWatson) #EmmaWatson  British actress and activist. Appointed as a UN Women Goodwill ambassador in 2014. Started her own #feminist book club in 2016: Our Shared Shelf.pic.twitter.com/Bj6RtGxryL

3. Yara Shahidi (@YaraShahidi) #YaraShahidi  American actress, model, and activist. Outspoken advocate for diversity in Hollywood and the importance of education for girls. Formed Yara's Club, which aims to bring high school students together to discuss social issues.pic.twitter.com/fe9ADntIuO

2. Malala Yousafzai (@Malala) (@MalalaFund) #MalalaYousafzai #Malala #MalalaFund  Pakistani #activist for female education. Miraculously recovered after being shot by a member of the Taliban at the age of 13. Youngest Nobel Prize holder.pic.twitter.com/obgmhg5NNd
1. Michelle Obama  (@MichelleObama) #MichelleObama  First African American First Lady. Also an author and lawyer. Graduated from #Harvard and #Princeton University.pic.twitter.com/ViVQCNAlB4
